            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </table>
 You can create a surface called a
 Coons surface patch, a mesh connecting four edges. You select the entities that define the edges. Edge
 entities can be arcs, lines, or polylines. The four edge entities must form a closed
 loop and share
 endpoints.A patch is a bicubic
 surface (one curve extends in the M-direction and the other in the N-direction) interpolated between the four adjoining edges.
 You can select the edges
 in any order. The first
 edge you select determines the M-direction of the mesh.</p>
      <p>
        <table>
          <tgroup cols="1" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
            <colspec colname="c1" align="left" />
